body:
Innocence

Chapter 1

Genre: Gang Au, Angst, Fluff (Later)

Future Pairing: Taehyung x Reader

Warnings: Alcohol consumption, swearing, violence/murder/death, kidnapping

Summary: When you find yourself in the wrong place at the wrong time, people have to take safety measures to make sure that you didn’t see anything. If you did, they’ve got to make sure you keep your mouth shut. What better way of doing that than to make you disappear. But this little disappearing act may have been an act of mercy because of a secret observer who happens to like you a little too much.

Word Count: 1.3K

“Come on (Y/N) it’ll be fun. When was the last time we had a girls’ night at a good club with cheap drinks?”

“You’re not going to let this go are you Lisa?” you ask your best friend as she scrambled through her wardrobe, looking for an outfit that was ‘suitable’ for the night.

“You know me too well,” she says with a small smile of victory on her face. She knew you would comply, she’s your best friend after all.

“Well, in that case, you’ve got to give me something to w–”

Before you could even finish your sentence, she hands you a tight mid length nude dress with thin straps.

You decided to wear a light coat of makeup, just a simple brown eye with a light nude lip, as high maintenance looks were more Lisa’s thing. By the time you were both ready for the night it was almost 10:30, so you thought an Uber would be the best mode of transport to the club, plus you were both wearing heels and public transport wouldn’t be the best choice.

When you arrived, the first thing you noticed was the large neon sign. DNA. Was this a new one? You’d never been here before. The two of you got out of the cab and made your way to the door which, surprisingly, didn’t have a line. Even though you would never admit it aloud, you were glad Lisa brought you along with her. You looked great and you were ready to have a good time.

The two of you made your way to the bar where you both ordered a few shots to start the night. As the bartender made your drinks behind the counter, you watched as your best friend beamed with excitement, clearly enjoying the atmosphere, dim lights and loud music. Shortly after, three small glasses and a slice of lime were placed in front of each of you and after sharing a sort look, the both of you down all your shots in unison, sucking the lime after.

“WHOOOOOOOOOOO!” you hear Lisa exclaim beside you and you can’t help but let out a laugh.

“I bet you’re glad you came, aren’t you?” she asked, but you ignore the question and pull her towards the dancefloor.

The song is loud and upbeat, causing crowding on the floor but you didn’t mind. The two of you dance as though you have no worries. As more young men and women approach the floor, dancing seductively, grinding on each other and touching each other way too much, it starts to get a bit hot and you start feeling claustrophobic.

“I’m going to get some air, okay,” you call out to Lisa who has found a tall guy to dance with.

She gives you a thumbs up, letting you know that she’s heard you, and continues to dance with the handsome stranger. You weave your way through the sea of bodies, rejecting advances from drunk men on the way. You make it to the door and decide to go around the corner to avoid blocking the entrance. Leaning against a dry wall, you take your phone out of your purse and check the time. It’s 12:43 AM but you don’t feel tired at all.

As you flick through various apps to pass the time as you cool off you hear speaking nearby. You were so focused on your phone that you hadn’t considered that you were possibly not alone in the quiet, poorly lit side street.

“Are you fucking with me right now?”

“You know we don’t play with our money.”

“I’m being nice here, if I were to call the others they’d shoot you on sight. You know that right.”

Not wanting to hear too much you decide that you’ve had enough air and it’s time to go back inside and forget everything you’ve already heard with a strong drink. Maybe that would have been possible if you had that thought ten seconds earlier. But what you hear next makes your ears ring and your blood run cold.

BANG!

Just one shot. Then silence. That’s all you hear. It’s so quiet but so deafening at the same time.

“No, it’s just the alcohol messing with me,” you say to yourself as you continue to retreat. But when you turn around, rather than walking into the main street as expected, you walk into a buff chested man with an unreadable expression on his face. Panic sets as you think that this man may be an accomplice to what you’ve just overheard.

“I swear I didn’t see anything. I was just getting some air and checking my phone. I was just about to go back inside and have a good time with my best friend. I swear I won’t tell anyone. Well, there’s nothing to tell because I didn’t actually see anything.” You ramble on and on but the man in front of you remains silent with the same expression unreadable on his face. He let you speak, standing completely still and silent until you had nothing else to say and all that was coming out was a series of wheezes.

“I’ll assume you’re done now,” the man finally said as he took a step closer to you.

Reflex makes you step back, but before you can make a full step he grabs hold of your wrist.

“I’m pretty sure that what you’re saying is true and you didn’t see anything, considering I too cannot see from this angle, but I still have to take you with me. You know, can’t be too careful.”

SHIT

You try to pry your wrist away from his grip but its no use. He’s too strong.

“I’d save my energy if I were you.”

And with this, tears begin to stream uncontrollably down your face. For some strange reason, perhaps to avoid further embarrassment, you turn your face away from him as you cry. He, on the other hand, seems completely unbothered by your tears and reaches for his phone in the right back pocket of his dark jeans. You faintly hear him speaking to someone of the phone, but you can’t quite stop the tears enough to concentrate on what it is he is saying, so when a black car with dark tinted windows pulls up around two minutes later you assume he called a getaway car.

Within a matter of seconds, your hands and feet are bound together by a pair of zip lock tags and you’re being placed in the back seat of the car. All that can be heard from you know are quiet whimpers as the realisation that you are now being kidnapped comes crashing down like a tonne of bricks. As you make the long drive to your unknown destination, you feel your eyelids grow heavy and soon you find yourself drifting into a dreamless slumber.

After some time, you feel yourself being lifted bridal style out of the car by one of the men, shaking you back to reality. The sun is yet to rise as you approach an extravagant looking mansion nicer than any building you’ve ever even walked past, let alone entered. As the double door open, you’re greeted with a well-lit foyer, stylishly decorated with a great staircase in the middle leading to a second floor. You’re still busy taking in our surroundings when a man speaks.

“Untie her and put her down Jungkook,” he says in a calm but commanding way.

“So, my kidnapper’s name is Jungkook,” you thought.

With this, the tension in your wrists and ankles is no longer present and you are being placed onto the white marble floor. Still, in your heels, you make a small ‘clink’ noise as you land.

“Hello (Y/N), I’m Namjoon. Welcome to your new home.”

Author’s Note: Helloooooooooooo! thank you so much for reading my very first fanfic. I know there are definite improvements that need to be made but I hope you enjoy it. I will make a masterlist as soon as I figure out how to do that :)

“I’d save my energy if I were you.”

And with this, tears begin to stream uncontrollably down your face. For some strange reason, perhaps to avoid further embarrassment, you turn your face away from him as you cry. He, on the other hand, seems completely unbothered by your tears and reaches for his phone in the right back pocket of his dark jeans. You faintly hear him speaking to someone of the phone, but you can’t quite stop the tears enough to concentrate on what it is he is saying, so when a black car with dark tinted windows pulls up around two minutes later you assume he called a getaway car.

Within a matter of seconds, your hands and feet are bound together by a pair of zip lock tags and you’re being placed in the back seat of the car. All that can be heard from you know are quiet whimpers as the realisation that you are now being kidnapped comes crashing down like a tonne of bricks. As you make the long drive to your unknown destination, you feel your eyelids grow heavy and soon you find yourself drifting into a dreamless slumber.

After some time, you feel yourself being lifted bridal style out of the car by one of the men, shaking you back to reality. The sun is yet to rise as you approach an extravagant looking mansion nicer than any building you’ve ever even walked past, let alone entered. As the double door open, you’re greeted with a well-lit foyer, stylishly decorated with a great staircase in the middle leading to a second floor. You’re still busy taking in our surroundings when a man speaks.

“Untie her and put her down Jungkook,” he says in a calm but commanding way.

“So, my kidnapper’s name is Jungkook,” you thought.

With this, the tension in your wrists and ankles is no longer present and you are being placed onto the white marble floor. Still, in your heels, you make a small ‘clink’ noise as you land.

“Hello (Y/N), I’m Namjoon. Welcome to your new home.”

Author’s Note: Helloooooooooooo! thank you so much for reading my very first fanfic. I know there are definite improvements that need to be made but I hope you enjoy it. I will make a masterlist as soon as I figure out how to do that :)
